        <div class="studio-tab-panels">
            <div class="studio-tab-panel studio-tab-panel--active studio-tab-panel--entrance" id="tab-approach">
                <p>The traditional agency model was built to scale. We were built not to.</p>
                <p>Small means the people responsible for your work are the people accountable for it. No layers to absorb the feedback, dilute the thinking, or slow things down.</p>
                <p>We understand the problem before we propose the solution. The structure we build is earned, not imposed. The work that comes out the other side doesn't chase what's current; it's <span class="award-name" data-award-pop>award-winning</span> because it's built to outlast it.</p>
            </div>
            <div class="studio-tab-panel" id="tab-founder">
                <p><span class="founder-name">Pierce Liefeld</span> founded COGNAK with a simple premise: there's no reason a small studio can't do what a large agency does — usually better, and without the overhead baked into the cost.</p>
                <p>An MFA in sculpture and years of work across brand, digital, and development mean the taste and the range are real. A tight network of developers, motion designers, 3D artists, and production specialists means the scope is too. The difference is you work directly with the person responsible for all of it.</p>
